concept("colorScale",|std:///experiments/RascalTutor/Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/colorScale/colorScale.concept|,[],[],{},"","",""," \<code\>Color(&amp;T &lt;: num) colorScale(list[&amp;T &lt;: num] values, Color from, Color to)\</code\>\n",{}," Gives a list of numbers, return a function that maps these numbers to a color scale between the colors \<code\>from\</code\> and \<code\>to\</code\>.\n"," \<pre class=\"listing\"\>observed = [10, 20, -50, 13, -40, 25];\ncscale = colorScale(observed, color(\"green\", 0.5), color(\"red\", 0.8));\nboxes = [ box( text(\"&lt;v\>\"), size(50), fillColor(cscale(v))) | v &lt;- observed ];\nrender(hcat(boxes));\n\</pre\> gives \<img class=\"TutorImg\"  title=\"h1\" alt=\"h1\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/colorScale/h1.png\"\>\n","","",[])